    "text": "Supreme Court strikes down federal sports betting ban, paving way for NJ and other states Michael Sheetz Reblog The U.S. Supreme Court rules that states can legalize sports betting. The court upholds the legality of a 2014 New Jersey law permitting sports betting at casinos and racetracks in the state. Nevada's Gaming Control board reported $4.8 billion in sports bets last year but Americans wager \"$150 billion illegally each year through off-shore, black market bookies,\" according to DraftKings CEO Jason Robins.",
